item.dc:creator: @Evade Evade
item.description:
@Evade wrote:

Don’t delete your whole client.java, just find the last thing you editted and change it back to normal, you stuffed something up in it, if you don’t remember what you editted, sorry but your screwed…[br][size=1]Posted on: August 24, 2007, 01:59:16 AM[/size][hr]Sorry 4 double post, i accidentaly hit enter.

When u compile, there should be some crap like:

Client.java: cannot find symbol.

then under that it says location, that location is where you messed up so just open your client.java and ctrl+f and search for what it says in the location and change it back to normal, if you don’t know where it’s stuffed up go back to your compiler and under the location writing there should be one of these : ^ and that’s pointing to the stuffed up part. but you have 100 errors so might take a while, or you could just re-install your whole client =)
